const VERSION = '2.9.276'; // v2.9.267 UPCOMING DATES - ROOT CAUSE FIX. The page rendered the right group names but zero events. Proven live: pcoGroupsForPerson scans EVERY group in the church (1 membership call per group, ~150 calls) just to find which ones the leader leads. That burns the entire PCO rate-limit budget inside one request; by the time buildGroupEvents fires its 11 membership calls to get the actual people, PCO returns 429, pcoGroupPersonIds hits "if (!r.ok) break", and every group comes back with zero people -> ids=[] -> no events -> "No birthdays or anniversaries are on file". Verified by firing the group scan three times in a row: run 3 degraded so hard that even the initial person lookup failed. v2.9.207 cached the DATES but left the MEMBERSHIP SCAN uncached, which is the expensive half. Fix: cache group membership in D1 too (pco_group_cache + pco_group_members), warmed by the existing admin Refresh button and the existing weekly cron. pcoGroupsForPerson and pcoGroupPersonIds now read D1 first and only fall back to the live PCO scan when the cache is cold, so a warm page load makes ZERO PCO calls and cannot be rate-limited. Additive: 2 tables + 2 cache-first prologues + warm wired into the existing button and cron. No route, no UI, no existing feature changed. Also fixes the monthly digest, which reads groups through the same two functions and has never sent (digest_log empty). // v2.9.266 SEND A COPY - the UI for the share endpoints shipped in v2.9.259-261 (server-only until now: /api/incident/share/send had exactly ONE reference in the whole file, the router line, so no client ever called it). New incidentSendCopyBlock(id) renders on incidentConfirmPage AFTER submit, so sendIncidentEmail (safety leadership) and sendSubmitterReceipt (filer) have already fired exactly once each - neither is touched or duplicated. Loads GET /api/incident/recipients: every PCO household shown separately and labeled, TabReady registry contact included, ALL boxes unchecked - nothing is ever preselected. Members with no email are shown but not selectable. Manual name+email entry always available. Optional collapsed reword field maps to external_note (changes only the external copy; the filed report is never rewritten). Preview is mandatory before send: POST /api/incident/share/preview renders the EXACT external page including the photo, then POST /api/incident/share/send issues the 45-day secure link per recipient. Neutral wording throughout - the person involved may be an adult or a child. Authorization unchanged and still server-side (canActOnReportShare): a volunteer may act only on a report they filed; resend/revoke stay with safety/staff/admin in the Reports tab. Back to Home still skips the whole step. Watch List untouched. // v2.9.262 INCIDENT REVIEW POLISH (no second review system). The pre-submit review modal in incidentFormPage ALREADY existed since v2.8 and already gates every email - this only fills its two gaps. (1) The attachment now renders a real thumbnail via URL.createObjectURL when the file is an image/*; non-image attachments (pdf/doc) keep the filename + size line, since the field accepts those too. Object URL is revoked before each re-render so repeated review taps do not leak. (2) NEW preview-occurred-row shows the recorded date/time from f-occurred, formatted, so the filer sees the time they are attesting to. (3) Buttons relabeled Submit Report / Edit Report per Shane 2026-07-16. The form trigger already read "Review & Send" - left alone. Save path, safety-leadership email (sendIncidentEmail) and filer receipt (sendSubmitterReceipt) are UNTOUCHED and still fire exactly once each. NOTE: personFormPage (Watch List) has its own separate confirm modal sharing the confirm-cancel id and the same button text - every anchor here was scoped to the unique confirm-send id so the Watch List modal was not touched. // v2.9.261 SHARE AUTHORIZATION IS PER-REPORT, NOT PER-ROLE + PHOTOS REACH THE RECIPIENT. Filing an incident report is open to every logged-in user, so sending the recipient copies that are part of filing is open too (Shane ruling 2026-07-16: volunteer through staff/admin). incidentShareGate is now just "signed in"; real authorization moved to canActOnReportShare(env,user,rid) - a volunteer may act ONLY on a report where reporter_user_id is theirs; safety/staff/global admin may act on any report. Applied to /api/incident/recipients, /share/preview, /share/send. Without it an open send path would let any volunteer email themselves any report in the system. Management stays privileged: /api/incident/shares (browse delivery activity) and /share/revoke now use incidentShareManageGate (global admin + safety + staff) - volunteers never browse or revoke others' shares. NEW GET /r/:token/photo serves the incident photo to an external recipient with NO login: token -> SHA-256 -> share row -> not revoked -> not expired -> photo_key resolved FROM that share's report_id (never caller-supplied), so a valid token reaches only its own report''s photo. Revoke or expiry kills photo access on the very next request. no-store, noindex, no-referrer, inline. loadReportForShare now selects photo_key; externalReportHtml renders a Photo section when opts.photo_url is set. Recipient page passes the tokenized URL; staff preview passes the authenticated /photo/ URL (same renderer, same content, only the image URL differs since no token exists pre-send). Existing safety-leadership email on submit untouched - not duplicated. // v2.9.260 INCIDENT CONTACT IS DATA, NOT CODE. Removed every hardcoded office@thetabsrq.net (a PHANTOM address - never created in Email Routing, no evidence of use). External report page + share email + expiry/revoked pages now read incident_contact_name / incident_contact_email from app_settings, seeded to 'Ronel Uys / Church Office' + ruys@thetabsarasota.org (verified active). An office administrator change is now a settings edit, not a deploy. Hardcoded fallback is the verified-active address, never the phantom. // v2.9.259 EXTERNAL INCIDENT REPORT SHARING - server layer (Builder packet 9-16). New additive table incident_shares (no existing schema touched). Neutral terminology throughout: person involved / recipient - NOT child-only or parent-only. GET /api/incident/recipients suggests recipients from ALL PCO household memberships + TabReady registry, every candidate checked:false, primary_contact/child/grade/age used ONLY as labels and data-quality warnings, never to select or exclude. Multiple households are shown separately and labeled; TabReady does not guess which is correct. POST /api/incident/share/preview and /send share ONE renderer (externalReportHtml) so the staff preview cannot drift from what the recipient sees. Recipients deduped by email before send. Staff may override the external-facing description; the internal report is never rewritten. GET /r/:token = public tokenized report page, NO login, 40-char token matched by SHA-256 hash, scoped to one share row = one report + one recipient, 45-day expiry, revocable, noindex/no-referrer/no-store. Excludes DB+PCO ids, tokens, audit rows, delivery metadata, staff permissions, third-party contact info. follow_up_needed Yes/No is preserved internally and translated to plain external wording. NO acknowledgment required of the recipient (/incident/ack untouched and still login-gated for staff). sent_at and first_opened_at/open_count tracked separately; opening is not agreement. // v2.9.257 SCHEDULE CONTACT SCOPE (Scout R3) + PROBE REMOVAL (Scout R5). /api/schedule now authorizes phone/email server-side per row: admin=all, your own row, teams you belong to, and designated team leads serving on a date your own editable team serves. Everything else gets phone/email dropped from the JSON. Names, teams, times, positions, blackouts unchanged. directory_optin is NOT used as the schedule authorization rule (Scout: directory consent and schedule-operation access are different purposes). Removed GET /api/pco-household-probe, its handler, and its temporary key path entirely - route and function are absent from live code, not just key-expired. No schema change. // v2.9.256 RACE FIX on the v2.9.255 edit gate. schedCanEditRole read USER_ROLES, which is declared empty and only filled asynchronously by /api/me. If the Schedule tab rendered before that fetch resolved, a team leader saw NO Remove/Swap buttons and the feature looked dead. Now reads MY_TEAM_ROLES (server-rendered inline, same data, synchronous) and falls back to USER_ROLES. Server canEditSchedule unchanged and still the only authority. // v2.9.255 SCHEDULE REMOVE + SWAP. Wires the orphaned schedDeleteSlot to real controls. Team leaders can now remove and swap people on their OWN teams (client gate mirrors server canEditSchedule exactly; server remains the authority). Add-then-remove ordering on swap so a failed add never leaves a day short-staffed. No schema change, no new endpoint - both /api/schedule POST and /api/schedule/:id/delete already existed and were already gated. // v2.9.251 PCO HOUSEHOLD PROBE (temporary, admin-gated, read-only). Adds GET /api/pco-household-probe so the family-notification build can be based on OBSERVED PCO permissions instead of assumption (Scout constraint: verify before relying). No schema change, no behavior change to any existing path. Remove once the household path is proven. // v2.9.239 CONTENT-ROUTING SPLIT (zero-behavior foundation, Scout-approved). Added D1 columns audience_roles + resource_contexts on content, backfilled = exact copies of role_tags (109/109, 0 mismatches; 2 untagged '[]' preserved). Code: userCanSeeContent now reads EFFECTIVE audience_roles (fallback role_tags) = ACCESS; new contentListedFor reads EFFECTIVE resource_contexts (fallback role_tags) = PLACEMENT; apiContentList (Resources listing) + apiWhatSee count now filter by contentListedFor. All three fields identical today => identical behavior. role_tags UNTOUCHED (rollback source). Snapshot: content_routing_snapshot_20260714. No retag/curation; director/safety_consultant untouched; category_key/admin-bypass/full-vis/direct-link unchanged. Rollback: point userCanSeeContent+contentListedFor back to row.role_tags (or restore snapshot).
// v2.9.238 Contact-scope correction (Scout-approved). Data: whos_who_leaders card retagged from 11 tags -> ['staff','elders'] (admin sees via bypass); removed team_leader/cafe/greeters/living_nativity/special_events/facilities/safety/safety_consultant + inert director, so the church-wide leadership roster no longer masquerades as a team resource on volunteer pages. Code: removed the now-orphaned 'Team Leaders & Key Contacts' reference link from the Facilities crew view (facStaffHTML) so it isn't a dead pointer. Ron's Senior Adult Ministry listing + his directory card UNCHANGED. My Team, team directories, Send a Note, emergency/medical/facilities contact cards UNCHANGED. Rollback: restore whos_who_leaders role_tags to [cafe,director,elders,facilities,greeters,living_nativity,safety,safety_consultant,special_events,staff,team_leader] + re-add the facStaffHTML reference block.
// v2.9.237 LABELS-ONLY clarity (Scout-approved, role/tier audit). Schedule->My Schedule (tile+heading); Connect->Updates & Notes (tile+drawer) w/ role-aware desc via USER_CAN_BROADCAST (base: 'Send a note to a leader.'; broadcast: 'Post an update or send a note.'); My Team desc->'People serving with you — your team contacts.'; Directory desc->'Staff and ministry-leader lookup.'; removed stale access-preview 'Approve Time Off/elders' entry (approval workflow retired in v2.9.124). NO tiles moved/hidden/merged; NO route/data/permission/gate change. Dead time-off helpers left as future cleanup debt.
