// v2.9.209 - Digest SCOPE switch. New app_settings 'digest_scope' = 'sunday_school' (default) or 'all_groups'. In all_groups mode every non-hidden Planning Center group's leaders get the digest EXCEPT names in 'digest_exclude' (newline-separated block-list of admin/governance/committee/one-off-event groups). Preview labels adapt to scope and list what's blocked. Changing scope or the block-list is a settings-only change \u2014 no redeploy. Still dormant behind digest_enabled. No other behavior changed.
// v2.9.208 - Upcoming Dates DIGEST reworked: (1) cadence is now TWICE MONTHLY on the 1st (covers 1\u201314) and the 15th (covers 15\u2013end of month) instead of once on the 25th; (2) scoped to SUNDAY SCHOOL classes only (match term in app_settings 'digest_ss_match', default 'sunday school'; matches group name OR Planning Center group-type name) \u2014 every other PCO group is excluded and listed; (3) Preview now reports eligible classes + resolved leader recipients/emails, classes with no leader, leaders with no email, excluded non-SS groups, and final counts \u2014 nothing is silently skipped; anniversaries auto-included when present. Shipped dormant (digest_enabled forced OFF on this deploy). Cron trigger is the go-live gate. Additive/rewrite within the dates block only; live leader view /my-groups/dates unchanged.
// v2.9.207 - Upcoming Dates / digest RELIABILITY FIX. Root cause: Planning Center does NOT return birthdate/anniversary in the group-membership payload (only via a per-person GET), so loading a leader's many groups fired hundreds of per-person calls per page and blew PCO's rate limit — every date came back empty. Fix: new D1 cache pco_dates_cache stores each person's month/day once; the view and digest read from cache instead of hammering PCO. Cheap membership calls resolve who's in each group; a bounded per-person fetch (cap 80/load) warms the cache and self-heals as leaders use it. New admin button 'Refresh dates from Planning Center' (/api/dates/refresh) + weekly cron warm keep it fresh. Digest preview/test now read cache (fast); a real send warms first. Additive: 1 table + 1 route + 1 button + cron warm. No existing feature changed.
// v2.9.206 - UPCOMING DATES + MONTHLY DIGEST (birthdays & anniversaries). New group-scoped static view /my-groups/dates: a group LEADER (Sunday school teacher / team leader) sees their group's upcoming birthdays & anniversaries (This month / Next month / Next 30 / Next 60), month+day only (no birth years/age), with the same Call/Text/Email/Save contact chips. Sourced live from Planning Center (birthdate + anniversary). Also ships a monthly email digest engine that emails each group's leaders next month's dates — shipped DORMANT behind an admin toggle at /admin/dates (default OFF) with Preview + 'Send me a sample' so nothing reaches a leader until Shane previews and turns it on. Minors excluded from the digest by default (toggle). People can be hidden via date_prefs. Additive: 5 routes + 1 button on /my-groups + scheduled() hook + new tables date_prefs & digest_log + app_settings flags. No existing route/feature changed.
// v2.9.205 - Account Health (READ-ONLY, admin only): new Admin Tools screen /admin/account-health. Scans every TabReady account against Planning Center by email and reports matched / wrong-or-other-email / no-PCO-record / duplicate-email-risk with a plain fix list. No writes to D1 or PCO; no auto-heal. Additive: 1 route + 1 nav link + 1 handler.
// v2.9.204 - PCO rate-limit resilience: all Planning Center reads now retry on HTTP 429 (respecting the Retry-After header, capped backoff, up to 3 tries) instead of failing instantly. Fixes Groups/Small Groups showing 'Couldn't read Planning Center groups: pco_http_429' during brief PCO throttling. Applies to pcoGetAll (groups/lists pagination) and pcoFetch1 (per-group membership loads in My Groups).
// v2.9.203 - Groups: shortened the non-linked-member empty state to plain, minimal copy ('No groups to show yet. Reach out to the church office and we'll connect your account.').
// v2.9.202 - Groups: rewrote the regular-member empty state. When a volunteer's account isn't linked to a Planning Center person, the old copy used insider jargon ('match your sign-in to Planning Center', 'make sure your TabReady email matches your Planning Center email') and read like it was still loading ('yet'). New copy is plain and actionable: groups show once the account is linked to their church profile, and if not, reach out to the church office. Admin/staff/elder branch (2.9.201) unchanged.
// v2.9.201 - Groups: admins/staff/elders no longer dead-end on a failed PCO email match. When their sign-in email doesn't match a Planning Center person, they still get the full 'See all church groups' view instead of the 'couldn't match' error (fixes Julie, a global admin, seeing no groups). Regular members still get the match-your-email message.
// v2.9.200 - Easy code login: enter email -> get a 6-digit code -> type it in the app. Whole flow stays in one browser context, so the login cookie lands where the app is used (fixes Gmail/in-app-browser users like Mary who had to sign in repeatedly). New login_codes table, /auth/code/request + /auth/code/verify (15-min, single-use, 5-attempt cap, generic responses). Login page swapped to the two-step code UI. Magic-link endpoints kept for onboarding/relink.
// v2.9.199 - Rolling session refresh: /api/me (hit on every app open via loadMe) now re-mints the login cookie, so EVERY active user rolls onto the 400-day key without re-login. Closes the gap where v2.9.198's longer key only applied to brand-new sign-ins. Mirrors the refresh /auth/me already did. Logout path untouched.
// v2.9.198 - Login persistence: session lifetime raised from 30 days to 400 days (~13 months), the browser hard cap for persistent cookies. Volunteers stay signed in well past a full year instead of being bounced to the email sign-in link monthly. One-constant change; token exp + cookie Max-Age both derive from it.
// v2.9.197 - Groups: 'Church Members' (whole-church list) now visible only to staff, elders, and admins; hidden for regular leaders/volunteers. Applies to list + detail. Preview endpoint gains &whole=1.
