//   Ronel) with no code change. New table: time_off_recipients. Additive.
// v2.9.120 — FIX: the v2.9.119 Time Off handlers used single-backslash quote
//   escapes inside onclick/onchange strings. Those collapse when the server
//   template literal renders, producing invalid client JS that broke the WHOLE
//   inline script (clock/weather stuck, Receipts + Time Off tiles never revealed).
//   Rebuilt those strings with String.fromCharCode(39) — no backslashes. No other
//   change from v2.9.119.
// v2.9.119 — Time Off form redesigned to match the inherited PTO form, but made
//   easy to fill out on a phone. Pick a type (Vacation/Sick/Personal/Holiday =
//   V/S/P/H, same legend as the paper form), add a date range, then tap to remove
//   any days you don't want off (e.g. weekends) — no calendar grid to wrestle.
//   Each day carries its own code (defaults to the chosen type) and the total day
//   count is figured automatically. Supports non-contiguous days (e.g. Feb 3-6 + 9-10).
//   Stored as days_json + total_days on time_off_requests (plus the existing
//   start/end/type columns for display + sorting). NOTE: re-run the updated SQL —
//   the table now has two more columns. Still confirm TIME_OFF_NOTIFY_RECIPIENTS.
// v2.9.118 — Added a staff-only Time Off tab (initial version; never deployed).
// v2.9.117 — Removed the "Next: ..." event line under the green header (it pulled
