// v2.9.111 — Schedule rework for non-tech users. Server-side grid parsing (import
//   works even if the phone runs a stale page); after import the calendar jumps to
//   the scheduled month; plainer labels; availability gets From/To labels, a one-tap
//   "whole shown month" fill, and a visible list of who's blocked with remove. App
//   HTML served no-store so the latest version always loads. Builds on v2.9.110
//   (tolerant name matching, unavailability flagging).
// v2.9.105 — Feedback fixes. (1) Directory is now collapsible: each team is a
//   tappable card, collapsed by default — no more endless scroll. (2) The
//   Connect/Safety corner marker is a clean chevron that flips ▾/▴ on open,
//   not a "highlighted dot". (3) Push is now discoverable: a "Push notifications
//   on this phone" Enable button sits on the Schedule tab (works on Android),
//   in addition to the Alerts-tab card.
// v2.9.104 — Web push actually works now. (1) Real RFC 8291 aes128gcm payload
//   encryption (the old code sent plaintext labeled as encrypted, which browsers
//   silently reject). (2) Service worker rewritten: handles 'push' +
//   'notificationclick', with NO fetch handler so it can never cache a stale
//   shell. (3) Re-enabled the "Enable push notifications" flow (was hard-disabled
//   in v2.9.56). (4) New sendPushToUser; schedule add/import now push the
//   scheduled person (independent of the email opt-in). REQUIRES two secrets on
//   the worker: VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY and VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY (push stays dormant and
//   harmless until they are set).
// v2.9.103 — Scheduling notifications. (1) In-app "You're scheduled" banner on the
//   Home screen on open, listing your upcoming serving dates (NEW pill for newly
//   added, dismissible, tap to open Schedule). (2) Opt-in email: a toggle on the
//   Schedule tab ("Email me when I'm scheduled", OFF by default); when on, that
//   person gets a summary email on import/add via Resend (best-effort, ctx.waitUntil).
//   New: users.notify_email column (default 0), /api/my-schedule, /api/me/notify,
//   sendScheduleEmail. Additive; the only schema change is one opt-in column.
// v2.9.102 — Church Calendar view (Planning Center events, event-card styling,
//   visually distinct from the Schedule month grid), leader Directory
//   (/api/directory: staff/elders/admin see all teams; a team lead sees their
//   own team's contacts — tap to call/email), and launcher cleanup: the
//   confusing "N in" drawer badge on Connect/Safety is now a ▾ expand chevron.
//   Both new tiles gated to leaders via USER_IS_LEADER. Additive: 1 endpoint,
//   1 route, 2 tabs, 2 tiles, 1 helper, led_roles on the user object. No schema change.
// v2.9.101 — Self-serve schedule upload for team leaders. Import now (a) accepts
//   a chosen .xlsx/.csv file (parsed client-side to CSV, no hand-editing), and
//   (b) resolves each name to a real user account so scheduled people are LINKED
//   (prerequisite for "my schedule" + notifications). Ambiguous/duplicate names
//   are left unlinked (user_id='unlinked') and reported back, never guessed.
//   Additive: same /api/schedule/import route, 3 client fns, 1 file input. No schema change.
// v2.9.98 — Onboarding QR Gallery (global-admin only). New page at /admin/onboard
//   lists all users with a search box; tapping a person mints a fresh SINGLE-USE
//   login QR valid 7 days, shown on the admin's phone for in-person scanning.
