// v2.9.94 — Header overflow fix. The right-side meta column (clock, date, and
//   the control buttons) was set to never shrink (flex:0 0 auto), so on a phone
//   it pushed past the green card's right edge and the clock/gear clipped off
//   screen. Now flex:0 1 auto so it shrinks and the buttons wrap inside the
//   card; the header also clips to its rounded box as a safety net. Pure layout
//   CSS — no color, content, auth, data, or behavior change.
// v2.9.93 — Follow-ups to the 2.9.92 map viewer + header logo:
//   (1) MAP ROTATE now works and fits: the Rotate button cycles 90 degrees and
//       re-fits the image to the screen (long edge fills), so a wide floor plan
//       is readable sideways on a portrait phone. The viewer also auto-rotates
//       with the device where the browser allows it (it unlocks orientation
//       while a map is open and re-locks to portrait on close); on a
//       portrait-locked iOS PWA the Rotate button is the reliable path.
//   (2) HEADER CONTROLS contrast: the clock, theme toggle, and gear were white
//       on the pale-green header and washing out. They now sit in a solid green
//       pill with a text shadow on the clock/date. Scoped to .header-controls
//       so the bottom nav is unaffected. No color/layout change elsewhere.
//   No auth/data/schema/route change. Built on 2.9.92.
// v2.9.92 — Two additive UI features. No auth, data, schema, route, or
//   permission change; built on the live, complete 2.9.88.
//   (1) FULL-SCREEN MAP VIEWER: tapping an image map opens a pinch-zoom /
//       drag-pan / rotate overlay so room numbers read on a portrait phone.
//       Self-contained client fns (buildMapViewer/openMapViewer) that build
//       their own overlay + styles on first use — no markup/CSS edits. PDF
//       maps keep their native new-tab open. renderMapGrid structure, the
//       scoped section ids, accordion (toggleMapSection), and toggleMapDesc
//       are untouched; image cards only gained one onclick attribute.
//   (2) Header TabReady logo is now tappable -> showTab('home') (reuses the
//       existing Home nav). Cursor + tap-highlight only; no new nav logic.
//   NOTE: the un-deployed 2.9.89-91 login work (resend card, scanner-safe
//   login, QR) is NOT in this build — it is being rebuilt separately on a
//   clean base after the only saved copy was found truncated.
// v2.9.88 — Facilities maps: one viewer list for broad + safety (MAP_VIEW_ROLES).
//   Fixes the director seeing a different map set than the team — root cause was
//   the safety-map folder excluding 'staff' (the facilities director's role) and
//   the gate keying on 'director'/'facilities' roles that no user actually holds.
//   Both folders now share one rule and can't drift. Server-side only.
// v2.9.87 — Call cards now name WHO you're dialing. Every tile that surfaces a
//   phone number shows a small label above it (e.g. "Eric Wyrosdic · Safety Lead",
//   "Sarasota County Sheriff · Non-emergency", "Christine Follman · Medical"),
//   driven by one directory map (PHONE_DIRECTORY / labelForPhone) so the label is
//   identical on every role page — Safety, Sunday School, Facilities, all of them.
//   Render-only + one lookup table; no content or schema change. Unknown numbers
//   simply show the number with no label. No regex, no backticks (template rule).
//   (Companion D1 work, same session — data only, no code: removed the redundant
//   Incident Codes cheat-sheet; pulled the Buildings/Rooms reference off the
//   volunteer pages; de-duplicated the Parking cards; dropped the 6:00 PM line;
//   merged Code Blue + Choking + Overdose into ONE medical card with every
//   protocol inside; and made Sunday School identical to Safety — both now see
//   the same 61 cards. One source of truth; prune per role later if needed.)
// v2.9.86 — Two fixes.
//   (1) Bottom nav now appears on EVERY non-Home screen. The has-botnav toggle
//       was running at the END of showTab, after the per-tab loaders; if a loader
//       (Schedule, Team) threw, the toggle never ran and the bar was missing on
//       that page. Moved the toggle ABOVE the loaders so nothing can suppress it.
//   (2) Maps: General/Whole Campus and Safety-only maps no longer display the
//       auto-attached written note (every one had been mislinked to the same
//       Sanctuary responder note). Those maps are read for the image itself, so
//       the note is hidden there. Building-specific maps (Sanctuary, FLC, etc.)
//       keep their notes, and the admin "Change note" controls remain everywhere.
// v2.9.85 — Navigation pass. A persistent nav bar is now pinned to the bottom of
//   every screen (hidden only on Home). It carries a labeled "← Back" that runs
//   the SAME one-level-back logic as the phone's hardware back button, plus a
//   labeled "🏠 Home". Because it's pinned to the bottom, Back/Home are reachable
//   at the end of long dropdowns and lists without scrolling back to the header —
//   the "close at the bottom" behavior, generalized into one consistent control
//   everywhere. The header Home button also now always shows its "Home" label so
//   it explains itself instead of being a bare house icon. Additive only: showTab,
//   navGoBack, the in-page back-inline links, and every per-section accordion are
//   left untouched.
// v2.9.84 — Facilities Director "Maps" button now opens the real Maps gallery
//   (the brown building-accordion view in the facilities tab) — the SAME gallery
//   the Safety drawer's Maps button opens. It was previously wired to run a text
//   search of notes (facQuickSearch('Maps')), which is why the Facilities
//   Director only ever saw the notes list and never the gallery. The 'director'
//   role already has gallery permission (canSeeFacilitiesMap), so this is a pure
//   wiring fix — one button, one shared gallery, one standard everywhere.
// v2.9.83 — Maps: collapse the synced note behind a tap-to-open toggle so an
//   expanded building section shows clean map cards (matching the Safety grid)
//   instead of dumping every note's full text inline. renderMapGrid is shared
//   by BOTH the broad (Facilities) and safety grids, so this single change
//   unifies them — one standard, one and the same. New toggleMapDesc() handles
//   the open/close. No structural/data change; note text and routing untouched.
// v2.9.82 — Sync notes to maps. A map's note can now be LINKED to an existing
//   content note instead of retyped, so the Maps tab and the written notes are
//   one source of truth. Linked content renders live under the map and is shown
//   only to viewers allowed to see that note (its role_tags), so Safety and
//   Facilities see the same map info with no leakage. Admin tools: a per-map
//   note picker in the editor, plus a one-tap "Auto-link maps to notes" that
//   attaches each building's matching note (skips maps already linked or noted).
//   New endpoints /api/facilities-maps/notes (GET) and /api/facilities-maps/
//   autolink (POST), both global-admin gated.
// v2.9.81 — Map descriptions. Each facilities map can now carry a written
//   description that travels with it. Stored in D1 table map_descriptions,
//   keyed by the map's R2 key, so a note inherits that map's existing
//   broad/safety visibility — anyone who can see the map sees its note, no one
//   else, with NO new permission surface. Admins get an inline "Add/Edit note"
//   editor on each map card; everyone permitted sees the note under the image.
//   New endpoint POST /api/facilities-maps/describe (global-admin gated, key
//   restricted to the two map folders like delete). Deleting a map also clears
//   its note. No change to existing maps, storage, or open behavior.
// v2.9.80 — Building-name consistency. Map building labels now match the locked
//   campus list: "Foundations School" -> "Foundations Montessori" and
//   "Admin Offices" -> "Admin Building (school + some church staff)". Added the
//   missing "Maintenance Building". DISPLAY LABELS ONLY — the building slugs
//   (admin-offices / foundations-school) are unchanged, so every map already in
//   R2 stays grouped exactly as before. Maintenance is a new, additive slug.
//   No schema, permission, storage, or open-behavior change.
// v2.9.79 — Admin "Add Person" onboarding. New admin-only screen (Admin tab)
//   creates a user from a name + phone OR email, assigns their access (teams),
//   optional global-admin, and generates a one-tap login link to text them on
//   the spot. Backed by POST /api/admin/users (global-admin gated). Login is by
//   token so no inbox is needed; a placeholder email is synthesized if only a
//   phone is given. "Tier" = the access/teams selected — that's what controls
//   what they see (content tier never gated users).
// v2.9.78 — Incident report emails now ATTACH the photo. The report stored the
//   photo all along; the email builder was passed has_photo but never the key,
//   so it silently dropped it. Added a reusable photoAttachment() helper that
//   pulls the image from R2 and base64-attaches it (recipients see it without
//   logging in). Falls back to a "view in Reports" note if the fetch fails.
// v2.9.77 — Removed the Sunday/Wednesday/Living Nativity/Events day filter from
//   Resources (it filtered a field empty on nearly all content). Filter functions
//   left dormant and guarded, so nothing breaks. Pure UI removal.
// v2.9.76 — Reports tab: "Recent Reports" -> "Reports Filed" (label only).
// v2.9.75 — Categorizer split: ops content no longer piles into one GENERAL
//   bucket. It now fans out into Quick Reference / Procedures / Setup &
//   Open-Close / Checklists / Schedules / Supplies / Parking / Café / Staff &
//   Contacts / Worship / Budget — each a small collapsible section. Header meta
//   column pinned so the clock, date, and gear never clip (long name ellipsizes
//   instead). Launcher Safety "Incident Reports" -> "Reports Log".
// v2.9.74 — REFERENCE/RESOURCES OVERHAUL. (1) Every content category now renders
//   as a collapsible section (carat, closed by default) — even 3-item groups — so
//   no more long-scroll wall. Sections auto-open during a search. (2) Day filter
