//   bodies. (5) "Reference" -> "Resources" (launcher + title). (6) Curriculum
//   removed from the launcher; now a button inside Resources -> Sunday School.
//   (7) Header fix: controls wrap + meta can shrink so the clock/gear never clip.
//   Maps photo+descriptions are NOT in this build (separate, needs a description
//   field at upload). Render-layer only; no schema/route/permission change.
// v2.9.73 — NOTE ROUTING IS LIVE (no more asking for emails). When a note is
//   sent, the lane now emails the right inbox, resolved from live D1: the role's
//   designated team lead, else global admins for triage (we never blast a whole
//   roster). "Not sure" -> admins. Lane dropdown values fixed to real role ids
//   (Sunday School -> ss_adult). Best-effort send: a failure is logged, never
//   blocks the post. Assigning a lead to a role is a one-row update -> that lane
//   then routes straight to them.
// v2.9.72 — WORDING + ROUTING POLISH (volunteer-friendly). Launcher "Communicate"
//   -> "Connect"; drawer: Broadcast -> "Post an Update", Flag to Leader -> "Send a
//   Note" (new subtitles). Team Note page -> "Send a Note" (new description,
//   placeholder, "Send Note" button) with a "Who should receive this?" lane
//   dropdown (Café Leader / Safety Leader / Facilities Director / Office /
//   Greeters-Hospitality / Sunday School / Elders / Staff / Not sure). Lanes map
//   to existing team visibility for now; true per-lane EMAIL routing is pending
//   per-lane addresses (Sunday School + Office mapped broad/"all" as a safe
