// v2.9.51 — Phase 2 web push notifications. Three additions:
//   (1) SERVICE WORKER: New push-capable SW at /service-worker.js. Handles
//       'push' events and shows a notification. Re-registers cleanly on each
//       page load without causing the 0-byte / reload loop (guarded by
//       sessionStorage version key so it only re-registers on version bump).
//   (2) PUSH SUBSCRIBE API: POST /api/push/subscribe saves a Web Push
//       subscription (endpoint, p256dh, auth) to push_subscriptions D1 table
//       keyed by user_id+endpoint. DELETE /api/push/unsubscribe removes it.
//       Both auth-gated. VAPID keys read from env.VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY /
//       env.VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY secrets. If secrets absent, subscribe returns
//       {vapid_missing:true} and client shows a plain message instead.
//   (3) PUSH FAN-OUT: apiAlertCreate now calls sendPushToAll() after saving
//       the alert. Fan-out is best-effort (ctx.waitUntil); a single sub
//       failure never blocks the response. Expired/gone subs (410) are
//       auto-deleted from D1. VAPID signing uses the Web Crypto API built
//       into the Workers runtime — no npm packages needed.
//   (4) OPT-IN BUTTON: Notifications tab now shows an "Enable push
//       notifications" button (only on browsers that support it). Tapping
//       calls Notification.requestPermission() + pushManager.subscribe(),
//       then POSTs the subscription. Button state updates live.
//   SETUP REQUIRED: Two Cloudflare secrets must be added before push works:
//     wrangler secret put VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY  (base64url uncompressed EC public)
//     wrangler secret put VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY (base64url raw EC private)
//   Generate with: node -e "const {generateVAPIDKeys}=require('web-push');
//     console.log(generateVAPIDKeys())"  (npm i -g web-push first)
//   No schema change needed (push_subscriptions table created separately).
